There's some great things to be said about The Airliner, but they're marred by a few important negatives. The Tuesday half-price pizza special is great. They have pretty reasonable pizza (especially compared to the rest of the downtown offerings) available weekly at a great price. There's lots of seating room, including an upstairs too. The waitresses have always been attentive and nice.  Sounds like a decent place, right? Unfortunately, there's a couple of (very fixable) bad aspects about eating and drinking at The Airliner that ruin its reputation. Does that pint glass feel heavy? That's because it is. The bottom of the glass is purposely extra thick to short you 3oz of drink; i.e. you're getting a 13oz "pint". Test this for yourself by ordering a tallboy can of beer with a glass. The other black mark on an otherwise fine place is the receipts. They print your whole credit card number on they copy they keep! Worse yet is management knows about the issue, but they aren't doing anything about it. Do yourself a favor and scribble out all the but last four digits of your card number before signing and leaving it on the table.  If these couple issues were resolved, this place would be easy to recommend.
